Round1 : kubernetes & Networking Foundation
Q1: What are different types of services in kubernetes?
A: Service provide stable networking and pod discovery. even if the pod restarts or change ip ,service provide conistent endpoint. 
There are three types of services:
1) Clusterip- Expose the service inside the cluster only(for pod-to -pod communication)
2) NodePort- Makes the service accessible outside the cluster using:<NodeIP>:<NodePort> (port range 30000–32767)
3) LoadBalancer- creates the cloud load balancer and routes traffic to NodePorts->Pod.

Q2: There is an EC2 instance in a public subnet; how will you migrate it to private subnet?
A: option 1:
1: Identify the ENI of your instance(EC2-Instances-Network Interface-Eni)
2:Stop your EC2 instance
3:Remove Public IP
4:Go to EC2-Network interface->Eni->Actions->change subnet->select private subnet->save and close
5: Start your EC2 instance
with this approach we have downtime butfor critical applicationrunning in production and to have zero downtime we can go with another approach
option 2:
1: go to EC2 Instance->Instance->Action-> create AMI
2: EC2 Instance->images->Ami->Select your Ami->create ec2 instance selecting your private subnet
3: If needed terminate your older instance.

